x4freetext: A storage-cell  cryostat  filled  by  liquid  4He  at
liquid-N2 temperature.  Target  cell  was made of 80
micron thick Kapton foil with diameter of 90 mm  and
each consisting of 3 x  3  array  on  9  rectangular
cells  with internal dimensions 20 cm x 20 cm (deep)
filled with the liquid scintillator NEA2132A.
The systematic uncertainty was dominated by
the  systematic uncertainty in the neutron-detection
efficiency, which ranged from ~ 5% for Eg = 68.5 MeV
to  26%  for  Eg = 24.6 MeV.  Other large sources of
6%), and the number of photons (a combination of the
tagger   focal-plane   live  time  and  the  tagging
measurements  was  performed  at  MAX-lab  in  Lund.
Tagged photons from 23 < Eg < 70 MeV  were  directed
toward  a  liquid  4He  target,  and  neutrons  were
